cs.SC, cs.MS, cs.CG, cs.LO, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new algorithm for computing cylindrical algebraic decomposition, which is a fundamental tool in symbolic computation.
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also likely as the paper proposes a new implementation of the CAD algorithm.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper deals with the computation of solution sets of Boolean combinations of subformulas, which can be seen as a geometric problem.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category as the paper deals with the decomposition of Boolean formulas, which is a topic in logic.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a divide-and-conquer approach to computing CAD, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures.
